parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Oil Consumption due to Faulty Piston Rings
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, causing the vehicle to stall or catch fire, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil level drops significantly between oil changes
oil warning lights appear on the dashboard
and the vehicle may stall or fail to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Timing Belt Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing belt failure can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to bent valves, engine failure, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine oil pressure sensor can cause the engine to stall while driving, leading to potential accidents and engine damage.
symptoms: The engine oil pressure gets too low
no warning is displayed in the Driver Information Module (DIM)
the car starts stalling while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, damage to property, and potential injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the electrical system can cause multiple safety-critical systems to malfunction, leading to unsafe driving conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Oil Consumption due to Piston and Pump Ring Design
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, potentially causing accidents or fires, and leaving drivers stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
which can lead to engine damage or failure if not addressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rodent Damage to Soy-Based Wiring Insulation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The use of soy-based materials in wiring insulation can attract rodents, causing damage to the electrical system, which can lead to electrical failures, engine stalling, or even fires.
symptoms: Rodents chew through the wiring insulation
causing damage to the electrical system
and potentially leading to safety hazards.
